              h2 Command Line Installation
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          h4 To run gitignore.io from your command line you need an active internet connection an environment function.  You need to add a function to your environment that lets you access the gitignore.io API.
          h3.normal
            span.icon-stack.tux-logo
              i.icon-sign-blank.icon-stack-base
              i.icon-linux.icon-dark
            |  Linux
          h4 #!/bin/bash
          pre.highlight
            span.nv $&nbsp;
            span.nb echo&nbsp;
            span.s2 "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/\$@ ;}"&nbsp;
            | >> ~/.bashrc&nbsp;
            span.o &&&nbsp;
            span.nb source&nbsp;
            | ~/.bashrc
          h3.normal
            span.icon-stack.apple-logo
              i.icon-sign-blank.icon-stack-base
              i.icon-apple.icon-light
            |  OSX
          h4 #!/bin/bash
          pre.highlight
            span.nv $&nbsp;
